From: cppmega mlx path-c <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 13:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(metal): keep simdgroup storage scalar for 32x32 pipelines

T.Pipelined(..., num_stages > 1) on Metal first needs the Metal macro
emitter to keep the software-pipeline leading stage dimension when forming
T.access_ptr indices.  After that fix, 32x32 accumulator fragments still hit a
separate Metal lowering failure: StorageRewrite can rewrite
metal.simdgroup pointer variables from scalar float/half element types to
vector element types such as float32x4 when later ramp accesses are observed.

That rewrite is not valid for Metal simdgroup matrix storage.  Metal codegen
lowers metal.simdgroup buffers to MSL simdgroup_matrix<T, 8, 8> arrays, whose
element type must remain scalar.  Keep those pointer element types scalar and
leave vectorization to the simdgroup load/store/mma intrinsics.

diff --git a/src/transform/storage_rewrite.cc b/src/transform/storage_rewrite.cc
index d494fdac..7b05d67a 100644
--- a/src/transform/storage_rewrite.cc
+++ b/src/transform/storage_rewrite.cc
@@ -1713,6 +1713,13 @@ public:
     // type.
     for (const auto &pair : info_map) {
       const auto &var_info = pair.second;
+      // Metal simdgroup buffers lower to MSL simdgroup_matrix<T, 8, 8>
+      // arrays.  The Metal codegen only accepts scalar matrix element dtypes
+      // (half, float, bfloat), so keep their pointer element type scalar even
+      // if downstream store/load patterns use ramp indices.
+      if (GetPtrStorageScope(var_info.var) == "metal.simdgroup") {
+        continue;
+      }
       DataType preferred = var_info.get_preferred_dtype();
       if (preferred != var_info.element_dtype &&
           (rewrite_mask & var_info.declaration_location)) {
-- 
